{"lemma":"كاسِر","slug":"كاسِر","root":"ك.س.ر","root_slug":"ك-س-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-س-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n36978"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%90%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36978","headword_ar":"كَاسِرٌ","root":"ksr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Breaking"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. masc. and fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kus~arN","text_ar":"كُسَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and pl. fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kawaAsiru","text_ar":"كَوَاسِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also (K.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Folding"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doubling, and leaning"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reclining upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a pillow or cushion. Hence the following. in a trad. of 'Omar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA yazaAlu A^aHaduhumo kaAsirFA wisaAdahu","text_ar":"لا يَزَالُ اَحَدُهُمْ كَاسِرًا وِسَادَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda A@moraA^apK mugoziyapK","text_ar":"عِنْدَ ا@مْرَاَةٍ مُغْزِيَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Not one of them ceases to fold"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"double his pillow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cushion at the abode of a woman whose husband is absent in war, and to lean"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recline upon it, and enter upon discourse with her."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)  An eagle, (A, K,) and a hawk or falcon, (A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contracting his wings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contracting them somewhat, so that he may descend in his flight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order to alight."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkaAsiru","text_ar":"الكَاسِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The eagle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K","TA"]}]}}